Introduction

Jay B (born Im Jae Bum) is a South Korean singer, songwriter, and actor. He debuted in 2012 as part of the duo JJ Project alongside Jinyoung under JYP Entertainment. In 2014, he became the leader of the seven-member boy group GOT7, later forming the sub-unit Jus2 with Yugyeom in 2019 and releasing the EP "Focus."

Following GOT7’s departure from JYP Entertainment in 2021, JAY B signed with H1GHR Music and made his solo debut. He left the label in July 2022 and later joined CDNZA Records, before parting ways in April 2023. Despite his solo pursuits, he remains the leader of GOT7 and oversees the group’s legal and official matters.
